    • Constructor Detail

      • CellConfiguration

        public CellConfiguration​(String nodeId,
                         boolean enabled)
        Creates a CellConfiguration for the node with the given {@param nodeId} and sets whether it is {@param enabled}. The maximum download and upload rates are set to Long.MAX_VALUE for this node.
        Parameters:
        nodeId - The id of the node
        enabled - Tells whether the node is enabled

      • CellConfiguration

        public CellConfiguration​(String nodeId,
                         boolean enabled,
                         Long maxDownlinkBitrate,
                         Long maxUplinkBitrate)
        Creates a CellConfiguration for the node with the given nodeId and sets whether it is enabled. The maximum download rate for the node is as set with maxDownlinkBitrate. The maximum upload rate for the node is as set with maxUplinkBitrate.
        Parameters:
        nodeId - The id of the node
        enabled - Tells whether the node is enabled
        maxDownlinkBitrate - The maximum download rate for this node
        maxUplinkBitrate - The maximum upload rate for this node
